# Community Project

## Introduction

Welcome to the Community Project! This project aims to manage the level progression of its members, from newcomers to seasoned contributors.

## How to Become a Contributor

Start by submitting a pull request (PR) to any of the official repositories under the Intalink organization. Once your PR is successfully merged, you're a Contributor!

## Level Progression

### Contributor to Member

- Contribute a valuable PR, such as an easy-level community development task.
- Express a willingness to maintain the community.
- To apply, open an issue in the community repo with a self-introduction and links to your contributions.

### Member to Committer

- Have at least 10 merged PRs, including either 1 hard-level or 4 medium-level PRs.
- Community consultation support.
- Active response to issues or PRs assigned to you.

## Responsibilities and Privileges

- **Contributors**: Submit PRs and engage with discussions.
- **Members**: Help with triaging issues/PRs and get involved in the decision-making process.
- **Committers**: Review and merge PRs, vote on significant decisions, and uphold the quality of the project.

## Promotion Process

To be promoted, members will need to show consistent contributions and participation in the project. When ready, members can request a review of their status by submitting an issue to the community repo.

## Code of Conduct

We abide by the [Contributor Covenant](https://www.contributor-covenant.org/). All members are expected to uphold these standards.

## Contact

For any questions or suggestions, please reach out to the core team at [community-email@example.com](mailto:community-email@example.com).

## FAQ

_Q: How often are promotion reviews?_
A: Reviews are conducted on a quarterly basis.

## Contributing Guidelines

Check out our [CONTRIBUTING.md](/CONTRIBUTING.md) for detailed instructions on how to start contributing to the project.

---

Thank you for being a part of our community!
